main event: An unidentified flying object was observed in the vicinity of Ketchikan, Alaska on December 13, 1960, with radar tracking confirming its presence for 45 minutes.
interesting points: The sighting involved an object that was flying and flickering in brightness,The object's altitude varied during the observation,The object was radar tracked, there is speculation it could have been a balloon or an aircraft,Some witnesses reported seeing two objects, one of which emitted a bright red light.
